main event: A luminous, oval-shaped object was observed in the sky over Treysa, Germany on November 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to be emitting a bright, white light.
It was observed for approximately 5-10 minutes before suddenly accelerating and disappearing from view.
No other witnesses were reported, and no physical evidence was recovered from the incident site.
The object was described as being about 6-8 meters in diameter and moving at an estimated speed of 600-800 kilometers per hour.
No sound was associated with the object.
